articles.title: Warning signs you are suffering from colorectal cancer - Daily Mail
articles.description: Candace Henley, 55, was diagnosed with colorectal cancer at age 35. While the cancer is often considered 'old man's disease' - the average age of diagnosis in the US is getting younger.
articles.content:
A woman diagnosed with cancer in her 30s is warning others not to ignore early signs of the disease, amid an epidemic of cases striking young people.
